34
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Even non-union members must pay dues that fund a union\rquote s working against efficiency measures such as merit-based pay, for example. Employees may disagree with this stance, which they describe as political, especially for public sector unions, where each negotiation affects public policy and the public fisc.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F35482421465_ID0EZ1AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F35482421465_ID0EZ1AE_1}
