 and these First Amendment claims are a pretext for partisan advocacy for policy goals. Business organizations and think tanks bringing these First Amendment claims are advancing radically new First Amendment positions because of their business interests, they claim. Religious objections to neutrally applicable laws on the claim that the religious objector does not want to take part in a sexually immoral activity are not truly religious, but political, some argue.
}
