. If LGBT individuals can simply get cakes elsewhere, then what Colorado\rquote s public accommodations law is doing is forcing a Christian baker to acknowledge the \u8220\'3fdignity\u8221\'3f of the LGBT community, which looks like more of a forced ceremony of tolerance and respect in the same way saluting the flag is a show of national unity and pride. However, if instead, public accommodations laws serve necessary economic functions, where \u8220\'3fsome citizens are singled out to bear significant costs of another\rquote s religious exercise\u8221\'3f
}
