 held that serving and maintaining a diverse population is a legitimate pedagogical goal of an academic institution, many have argued that mandated diversity statements force professors to swear loyalty to a particular view of diversity that maps onto political ideology in a way that resembles the unconstitutional loyalty oaths that professors had to sign in the 1940s and 1950s.
