 Universities, they argue, should not (and perhaps cannot if they are public universities) mandate that every professor share the same views of the importance of specific types of diversity that track membership in underrepresented groups, as opposed to emphasizing or prioritizing diversity of ideas or experiences, or even other legitimate, critical academic values that may exist in tension with the stated goal of diversity.
